        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13705.xml">letter from W. D. Crick, 24 February 1882</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In the event, CD did not go to London.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Laurel (<hi rend="italic">Prunus laurocerasus</hi>) produces prussic acid (hydrogen cyanide; HCN), which inhibits oxygen utilisation in many animals.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">The son was <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml">Francis Darwin</ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13705.xml">letter from W. D. Crick, 24 February 1882</ref> and n. 3).</note>      
